			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This is a question directed toward those Mages who I have seen state that SOE doesn't like soloing.
<br />

<br />
I was just wondering why this is so?
<br />

<br />
I'm not talking about soloers vs. groupers, time invested, etc.
<br />

<br />
I'm just wondering, honestly, what is so bad about liking to solo in an MMO environment? Isn't SOE effectively alienating a (quite large) market segment by refusing to see that soloing should not be looked at as a bad thing?
<br />

<br />
If Joe Q. Guy wants to solo, understands that he will not gain as much XP as with a group, and enjoys soloing, why should SOE not regard this as a valid playstyle?
<br />

<br />
Maybe I'm just not seeing something?
<br />

<br />
*EDIT* OK, I don't know why this was moved to Class Balance, I was just asking a general question, not ranting...<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://bellsouthpwp.net/H/a/Haverghast/lum-sig.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
