				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">As for soloing, I think this is a market strategy from Sony. If you solo you will eventually get bored and quit.
<br />

<br />
If they force you to group/raid you will get a lot of "friends" and the ties you have to those friends will keep you playing for years. Even though the game is since long obsolete and all you do is sit in guilchat and talk about the old days.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Lumbik wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Actual Quote From a RL Friend - "Yeah, I tried it and all. EQ seems cooler than DAoC... IF I could've started when everyone else did. I played the free month, but never got a group and everyone was rude just because I was new. Seems that's the way the game goes, so I just gave up and went back to DAoC." </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This I think annoys me most with EQ of today. I can't say I have experienced it myself but I know other people who has.
<br />

<br />
When I started everyone was friendly to the clueless noob (me) and spent huge amounts of time teaching me the basics and helped me get going.
<br />

<br />
Today everyone is hellbent on progression and there is little time to "waste" for many people since they need to "work hard".
<br />

<br />
Old timers who says it's so easy... doesn't know jack! It's extremely easy for their twink - Not the NEW player.
<br />

<br />
* The interface is a lot more complicated. Filters, pop-up menues, options etc. And in the middle of all... a MP3 player to confuse you while searching for that special window you were looking for.
<br />

<br />
* A newbie zone that used to drop a few different things you could sell to merchants, now drops tons of different things, many confusing nodrop items for some newbie quests you don't know anything about, or can't do because it's not your newbie-quest.
<br />

<br />
* There used to be "a few zones", now there are tons of them. and everyone you talk to use abbreviations and really don't want to start explaining what they mean since more questions are sure to follow.
<br />

<br />
* There are more NPCs. With every added expansion, there are some added quests, and since they don't seem to reuse NPCs you have quest NPCs everywhere talking about different things and you have no idea how difficult the quest is. Or if the reward is for your class.
<br />

<br />
* Some players think it's funny to grief noobs, especially if they ask "stoopid" questions. With a big population on every server, no one really cares about reputation anymore.
<br />

<br />
Oh well... I'm glad I'm not a true noob! <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
