			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not to contradict, but you are a bit off on your assesment chaos.  SOE didn't intend for anyone to effectively solo in PoP.  Don't get me wrong, I am in no way saying that no classes CAN solo, but it wasn't designed around the solo aspect.  This has been evident around all the changes made to experience flow solo vs. grouped for ALL classes, not just mages.  Although we can still somewhat effectivly solo in teir 1, anything past takes a little more effort than /pet attack and nuke as much as you can before the mobs breaks loose from the pet to attack you.  It's possible, just not as easy.
<br />

<br />
No other classes were given anything in PoP that they did not previously have simply to make PoP easier to solo.  Unfortunatly this also means that mages were not given any more real utilities to make soloing easier, and still require the pet to maintain the mob is some fashion (pet tanking, yo yo kiting, aggro kiting, etc) as just like the other classes, no new abilities were added. *edit* I mean in terms of general abilities.  Bard Fading Memories and things of this nature are definatly new and added with PoP, but the general idea of how these classes killed for experience did not change.
<br />

<br />
This is not to say that soloing as a mage is impossible.  It simply means that soloing in PoP past tier 1 is harder.  Any other content older than PoP is still soloable, and 61+ becomes even easier with the PoP pets.  This is not to say they are perfect, they are far from it.  However being that they are level 60 and put out decent DPS, most older content gets sliced and diced rather quickly.  Older expansion content may not satisfy everyone, but it is still very doable for decent exp flow at 65 depending on what zones and mobs you are after.  However, I am not saying this is good enough...
<br />

<br />
Heck, as it stands right now most groups can easily out exp the typical soloer in any PoP zone, as the exp modifiers have been adjusted to net less exp per kill solo than even grouping with one other person per person.  Necros have always had snare, bsts have always had slows, shaman have had slow longer(heh heh) and bards and druids have always been able to kite, and unfortunatly mages have always had pets...  what I mean is simply what I stated above about the pet being the mob control.
<br />

<br />
I have heard rumors about the new MS pet being released with GoD, and hopefully with the new pet defensive AA's soloing may be a bit more viable in PoP as a mage using these new abilities.  But, just as I stated above, no classes were given any real abilites they did not already have previously to make them so much more powerful than mages.  The mobs changed drastically, not the classes. 
<br />

<br />
Venerable Longfanz Beaztmaster Feral Lord</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
