				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Chaos, maybe you just don't understand about soloing, after the countless posts that have pointed all this out.
<br />

<br />
I use my pet exactly as intended.  I have it engage the mobs, while I burn them down.  That is how I solo.  I have great success in the grey, in Acrylia Caverns, in Fungus Grove, in Nurga/Droga, Crystal Caverns, Plane of Innovation.  Lots of zones.  I farm tradeskill items at least once a week soloing, with no problems whatsoever.
<br />

<br />
What I can't do, is have my pet engage a mob that's double and quad hitting for 600+.  This is what you're asking for.  This is what you're never going to get.  No player tank can do it.  You can't either.  Get over it.
<br />

<br />
I never once said I ever expect Sony to give us the zones where mages could solo, and other soloers can't.  You simply said that the ONLY way for mages to solo better was to give us bigger monster pets.  I disagree.  There are many other ways Sony could allow mages to solo better, without even touching pets.  If you can't see this, then you are very much thinking shortsitedly.
<br />

<br />
Yes, GoD is a raiding expansion.  If you don't raid, don't buy it.  If you feel the new AA's and new spells aren't worth it, don't buy it.  But to emphatically state that increased pet dps only benefits a raiding mage is absurd, and ignorant.  Increased pet dps helps the soloing mage, the grouping mage, and raiding mage.  The only mage it does not help is the "never log in because I spend my time being negative on the forums" mage.
<br />

