				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Konjure wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As for soloing, I think this is a market strategy from Sony. If you solo you will eventually get bored and quit.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
I think this answered my question more than anything.
<br />

<br />
I wasn't really asking as far as Mage soloing, just soloing in general, that's why I didn't know why the post was moved to Class Balance.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
Personally, I think this is a bad strategy for SOE to follow, but that's just my (educated) opinion I suppose. There are many who solo 99% of the time and enjoy that more than anything.
<br />

<br />
Of course, the flaw here is that, just because you solo, that doesn't mean you don't socialize. My RL friend who got me started in EQ has been playing since Beta and he solos most of the time (Necro player, of course <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /> ), however, he is in a guild, has tons of in-game friends, and loves the game just as he did when it started.
<br />

<br />
Personally, I play MMOs because I am the type of person who only plays through a single-player game once. With single player games, I blow through them in a week or two weeks tops, then I'm back to looking for a new game. With MMOs, I can take my time exploring and, basically, have infinite challenge. At least, that's <span style="font-weight: bold">one</span> of the aspects I like about MMOs. I feel like a lot of dyed-in-the-wool soloers feel the same way.
<br />

<br />
I just see comments like, "Why play an MMORPG if you want to solo?!" and that makes me wonder why people assume that just because you play solo, you aren't interacting. That isn't true.
<br />

<br />
Oh well, I was just wondering about the reasoning behind that attitude toward all soloers in general.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
