			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I would have to agree with Nalidini here.  I love soloing, but have tons of friends that I am always interacting with.  I am still trying to understand why SOE still seems to see the whole soloing thing as evil.  In Rytan's post, he alludes to 'soloing shouldn't be as good exp as grouping'.  I don't think anyone ever asked for soloing to be as good, just reasonable.  I cannot count the number of times I simply haven't logged on at all because I didn't have time to find a group - all I want is to be able to log on for an hour or so and get reasonable solo exp with some measure of safety (not just in a few zones like Droga that seem to be perma-camped).  Hmm, seems if I don't log on I can't be social, can I?
<br />

<br />
SOE should be careful in listening to it's customer base.  While the mage community may be small in comparison to some of the others, all it takes is a few well placed stones to cause some major ripples.  I personally have started at least 10 to 15 people playing this game, who have told others and so on.  I haven't moved on from Everquest yet because I still enjoy the game and don't see a more compelling alternative, however, I am thinking of leaving when I find one.  This is true for many of my friends as well.  I am very happy they are talking about working on pet improvements in the near future, but am waiting to see if they actually make real improvements to our class before I make any final decisions. Remember, Nintendo lost it's crown in the home console wars because they failed to evolve with the times (can we say expensive cartridges vs. inexpensive CD's).  While this may seem slightly off topic, I believe the analogy works.  This game has evolved to trash mobs quad hitting for 500+.  I don't expect my pet to be able to tank tier 2 mobs directly, and don't think SOE will improve pets innate power all that significantly, so the real solution is giving us defensive spells directly or from weapon procs.  One of the two things need to be done, or we really do reach an impasse.
<br />
Just something to give us a fighting chance.  The issue isn't just soloing ability, but survivability.  I know this has been beaten to death, but it really is our primary concern.  Now, let's repeat that wonderful mantra <span style="font-weight: bold">'OUR PETS ARE NOT STRONG ENOUGH TO JUSTIFY OUR LACK OF A DEFENSIVE SPELL'</span>.  Careful SOE, that snowball is getting very large.
<br />

<br />
Well, I've gone on long enough.  It's late, so I hope this is somewhat coherent.
<br />

<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_evil.gif" alt="Evil or Very Mad" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />"It's been said that the fear of the unknown is simply an irrational response to the excesses of the imagination."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
